The animation runs whenever `SplitReveal` mounts. Changing `mode` or forcing a remount (like the "Replay" button above) replays the sequence.

## Props

| Prop     | Type                            | Default          | Description                                          |
| -------- | ------------------------------- | ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `mode`   | `"lines" \| "words" \| "chars"` | `"lines"`        | Pick which SplitText grouping animates.              |
| `class`  | `string`                        | `""`             | Adds classes to the wrapping element.                |
| `as`     | `keyof HTMLElementTagNameMap`   | `"span"`         | Tag used for the wrapper (swap to `div`, `p`, etc.). |
| `config` | `SplitRevealConfig`             | `DEFAULT_CONFIG` | Optional per-mode overrides for duration/stagger.    |

### Config shape

`SplitRevealConfig` accepts partial overrides for each mode:

```ts
type SplitMode = "lines" | "words" | "chars";
type SplitRevealConfig = Partial<
	Record<
		SplitMode,
		{
			duration?: number;
			stagger?: number;
		}
	>
>;
```

```svelte
<SplitReveal
	mode="chars"
	config={{
		chars: { duration: 0.6, stagger: 0.02 },
	}}
>
	Future-forward Research
</SplitReveal>
```
